<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFD3D65D0DB6FD2D192D3398" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFD3D65D0DB6FD2D186B3510" blockId="5.[2044,2638,705,1132]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFD3D65D0DB6FD2D19B834FB" bold="true" box="[2044,2199,705,738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D02FBFD2D196E3510" authority="Temminck, 1840" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">Vespertilio blepotis Temminck, 1840</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="D0893CB2FFD3D65D021BFD1C186F3510" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3747914320" box="[2129,2368,752,777]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">
“ 
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFD3D65D0216FD1C19B63510" box="[2140,2201,752,777]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Java</collectingRegion>
,” 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D02F9FD1C186F3510" box="[2227,2368,752,777]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFD3D65D0DB7FCFC192D3398" blockId="5.[2044,2638,705,1132]" lastBlockId="5.[1426,2640,1139,2633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0DB7FCFC182C3528" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2045,2307,784,817]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">Miniopterus blepotis</taxonomicName>
was often considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D02A0FCDB188A3541" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2282,2469,823,856]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">M. schreibersii</taxonomicName>
. When the 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0DB7FCB219AC3566" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2045,2179,862,895]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">schreibersii</taxonomicName>
complex was split, 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D03D8FCB21B333566" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2450,2588,862,895]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">M. blepotis</taxonomicName>
became a valid species clearly different from the rest of Asian and Australian species in the complex: M. fuliginosus, M. eschscholtzi, and 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0227FC10182C3204" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1922" box="[2157,2307,1020,1053]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orianae">M. orianae</taxonomicName>
. This is supported by mtDNA sequence data from New 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D03ACFBC81B63325C" box="[2534,2636,1060,1093]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D02A1FBA718563275" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2283,2425,1099,1132]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">M. blepotis</taxonomicName>
. As with other members of 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0C1BFB9F17C2328D" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1617,1773,1139,1172]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
, taxonomic arrangement here should be considered provisional until an overall genetic study is completed. Currently, distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D038EFB761B6132A2" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2500,2638,1178,1211]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">M. blepotis</taxonomicName>
is unknown either at the continental level (specimens cited as 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0353FB2E18B132FA" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2329,2462,1218,1251]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">schreibersii</taxonomicName>
of southern 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0FDCFB05173F3313" box="[1430,1552,1257,1290]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0C68FB05179C3313" box="[1570,1715,1257,1290]" name="Cambodia" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0CB1FB0516543313" box="[1787,1915,1257,1290]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Thailand</collectingCountry>
could theoretically be 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D028FFB05180F3313" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2245,2336,1257,1290]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">blepotis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0379FB0518863313" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="1931" box="[2355,2473,1257,1290]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnater">magnater</taxonomicName>
, or fuliginosus) or on islands of Melanesia (samples of the 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0273FAFD180B332B" box="[2105,2340,1297,1330]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
are genetically quite different from 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD3D65D0C23FAD417EC3340" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1641,1731,1336,1369]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">blepotis</taxonomicName>
of New 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0D79FAD416B03340" box="[1843,1951,1336,1369]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Guinea</collectingCountry>
). Itis also unknown if it is actually a complex that includes more than one species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFD3D65D0FDDFA63185F305F" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" type="distribution">
<caption id="349E6667FFD3D65D0FDDFA63185F305F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735230" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5735230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735230/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" targetBox="[1428,2021,717,1132]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFD3D65D0FDDFA63185F305F" blockId="5.[1426,2640,1139,2633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFD3D65D0FDDFA63176833B1" bold="true" box="[1431,1607,1423,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Distribution.</emphasis>
Malay Peninsula, 
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFD3D65D0D01FA6316ED33B1" box="[1867,1986,1423,1448]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, Borneo, 
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFD3D65D0202FA6319A933B1" box="[2120,2182,1423,1448]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Java</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFD3D65D02DDFA63182233B1" box="[2199,2317,1423,1448]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
, some Lesser Sunda Is (Lombok and Timor) and 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0D55FA5E168E33D6" box="[1823,1953,1458,1487]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
(Seram, 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D0262FA5E19BB33D6" box="[2088,2196,1458,1487]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Ambon</collectingCountry>
, and Kai Is), New 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD3D65D03EFFA5E1B2433D6" box="[2469,2571,1458,1487]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Guinea</collectingCountry>
